<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Call-for-concept-notes-Collaborative-Adaptation-Research-Initiative-in-Africa-and-Asia-CARIAA" title="Call for concept notes: Collaborative Adaptation Research Initiative in Africa and Asia (CARIAA) " alt="link">Call for concept notes: Collaborative Adaptation Research Initiative in Africa and Asia (CARIAA) </a></h2>

	
					<p><b>Deadline: 4 April 2013&nbsp;&nbsp; </b>IDRC and the UK’s Department for International Development (DFID) are funding a new programme on climate change adaptation. The Collaborative Adaptation Research Initiative in Africa and Asia (CARIAA) began in 2012 and will run until 2019. CARIAA invites submissions of joint concept notes for the establishment of research consortia in three climate change hot spots: semi-arid regions, deltas, and glacier and snowpack dependent river basins.Find out more at <a href="http://www.idrc.ca/EN/Programs/Agriculture_and_the_Environment/CARIAA/Pages/default.aspx" target="_self">http://www.idrc.ca/EN/Programs/Agriculture_and_the_Environment/CARIAA/Pages/default.aspx</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/03/2013</span></p>
